overview: The user wanted to enhance their sleep questionnaire application by
  adding a database to store responses and an admin dashboard for data access.
  After evaluating the existing codebase, the agent proposed and implemented a
  solution using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for data storage. This included
  creating a  model, API endpoints for saving and
  retrieving data (including CSV export), and a simple admin dashboard. A key
  decision was to use a straightforward password-based authentication for the
  dashboard. The authentication approach was later refined to leverage Next.js
  middleware, simplifying the codebase and improving route protection. The agent
  also provided clear instructions for database setup and initiated the Prisma
  schema push to the database.
